obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (36072)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36072&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Service`
  line `Act, 1972.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (36073)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36073&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(a) "employer" means any person who employs any qualified person for doing any work in any`
  line `establishment and includes any person entrusted with the supervision and control of qualified persons`
  line `in such establishment.`
  line
  line `(b) "establishment" means--`
  line
  line `(i) any office, or`
  line
  line `(ii) any place where any industry, trade, business or occupation is carried on, and includes`
  line `any technical institution or training centre;`
  line
  line `(c) "national service" means any service which is likely to assist the defence of India and civil`
  line `defence or the efficient conduct of military operations and includes such social service as the Central`
  line `Government may, if it is of opinion that it is necessary for public purposes so to do, by notification`
  line `specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(d) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "qualified person" means a citizen of India who is ordinarily resident in India and who,--`
  line
  line `(i) has obtained a recognised medical qualification within the meaning of the Indian Medical`
  line `Council Act, 1956 (102 of 1956), or`
  line
  line `(ii) has obtained, or has passed an examination which entitles him to obtain, a degree of a`
  line `University or its equivalent qualification in any branch of engineering or technology or both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this Act, a qualified person who is resident in India shall be`
  line `deemed to be ordinarily resident there unless--`
  line
  line `(a) he is residing there only for the purposes of attending a course of education; or`
  line
  line `(b) the circumstances of his residence there are otherwise such as to show that he is residing`
  line `there for a temporary purpose only; or`
  line
  line `(c) he, being a person who was born or domiciled in any country outside India, has been`
  line `resident in India for less than two years.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (36074)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Liability of persons to be called up for national service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36074&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who--`
  line
  line `(a) is a qualified person at the commencement of this Act, or`
  line
  line `(b) becomes a qualified person after such commencement,`
  line
  line `shall, if he has not attained the age of thirty years at such commencement, or, as the case may be, on the`
  line `date on which he becomes a qualified person, be liable until he attains the age of thirty years, to be called`
  line `up for national service for a period of not more than four years.`
  line
  line `(2) The period of national service for which a qualified person shall be liable to be called up under`
  line `this Act shall begin from the date on which he is required by an enlistment notice served under this Act to`
  line `present himself to the authority specified therein and shall end on the day when his term of national`
  line `service is completed in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (36075)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Voluntary service in lieu of national service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36075&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a qualified person has been enlisted under`
  line `any other law for the time being in force, for service in one of the Armed Forces of the Union for a period`
  line `of not less than four years, he shall perform the service required of the members of that Force in lieu of`
  line `the national service required under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) If a qualified person has rendered or is rendering service, other than service in one of the Armed`
  line `Forces of the Union and such service is declared by the Central Government to be equivalent to national`
  line `service, the period of such service shall be deemed to be service in lieu of the national service required`
  line `under this Act and he shall (unless he has ceased to be liable under this Act to be called up for national`
  line `service), be liable to be called up for national service for such term as will, together with the service`
  line `completed by him, be equivalent to the term of service for which persons are liable to serve under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(3) If any qualified person has been enlisted as a member of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Indian Reserve Forces, regulated under the Indian Reserve Forces Act, 1888 (4 of 1888),`
  line
  line `(b) the Territorial Army constituted under the Territorial Army Act, 1948 (56 of 1948),`
  line
  line `(c) the Air Force Reserve or the Auxiliary Air Force Reserve constituted under the Reserve and`
  line `Auxiliary Air Forces Act, 1952 ( 62 of 1952),`
  line
  line `(d) the Indian Naval Reserve Forces raised and maintained under the Navy`
  line `Act, 1957 (62 of 1957), or`
  line
  line `(e) any other Force of the foregoing nature,`
  line
  line `he shall not be called up, so long as he continues to be a member of that Force, to render national service`
  line `under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that he shall, after he has ceased to be a member of such Force, be liable to render national`
  line `service (unless he has ceased to be liable under this Act to be called up for national service), for such term`
  line `as will, together with the actual service rendered by him as a member of that Force, be equivalent to the`
  line `term of service for which persons are liable to serve under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (36076)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Liability to complete interrupted service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36076&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `If any qualified person serving in the Armed Forces`
  line `of the Union ceases to serve therein before he has completed four years of such service, he shall, unless`
  line `he has ceased to be liable under this Act to be called up for national service, be liable to be called up to`
  line `serve for such term as will, together with the service completed by him, be equivalent to the term of`
  line `service for which persons are liable to serve under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (36110)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power of Central Government to direct a person to render service with the Armed Forces of Union or other national service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36110&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 3, the Central Government may,`
  line `by order, require a qualified person to render service in the Armed Forces of the Union or such other`
  line `national service, as it may specify in this behalf, for such period and at such place as may be specified in`
  line `the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (36078)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Discipline.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36078&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every qualified person enlisted under this Act for national service in the Armed`
  line `Forces of the Union shall, subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, be bound to serve in any`
  line `branch of the Armed Forces to which he is for the time being attached, and shall be subject to all laws,`
  line `rules, regulations and orders in force for the time being in relation to such branch.`
  line
  line `(2) Every qualified person enlisted for any national service, other than service in the Armed Forces of`
  line `the Union shall, subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, be bound to serve in any position or post`
  line `to which he is appointed for the time being, and shall be subject to all laws, rules, regulations and orders`
  line `in force for the time being in relation to such position or post.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (36079)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power of Central Government to require any employer to release qualified persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36079&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Government may, by order in writing, require any employer to release any qualified person for`
  line `employment in national service within such time as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an employer releases a qualified person for employment in national service, such employer`
  line `shall not be liable to pay the salary, wages and other emoluments, if any, of the qualified person for the`
  line `period during which national service is or has been rendered by the qualified person.`
  line
  line `(3) No contract, subsisting between a qualified person and his employer on the date of release of the`
  line `qualified person for employment in national service, shall be enforceable until such qualified person has`
  line `been discharged from national service.`
  line
  line `(4) In computing the period specified in any contract of service in relation to a qualified person who`
  line `has been called upon to render national service, the period of national service actually rendered by such`
  line `qualified person shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(5) If any employer fails without sufficient cause to comply with the order made under`
  line `sub-section (1), he shall be liable to be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three`
  line `years and also with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (36080)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title Transfer.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36080&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by regulations, make provisions for enabling or`
  line `requiring a qualified person rendering national service in any branch of the Armed Forces of the Union to`
  line `be transferred to any other branch of that Force or to any other branch of national service or vice versa.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (36111)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Persons not to leave national service or be discharged therefrom unless permitted by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36111&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) No qualified person rendering national service under this Act shall leave`
  line `such service until he is discharged therefrom under section 17.`
  line
  line `(2) No qualified person who has been served with a notice under sub-section (1) of section 13 or an`
  line `enlistment notice under section 14 shall, if he is in any employment at the date of service of such notice,`
  line `leave such employment or be discharged therefrom, except in accordance with the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply where the employment of a qualified person is`
  line `terminated for the reason that the said person has been guilty of gross insubordination, habitual absence`
  line `from work, or serious misconduct or has been convicted of an offence.`
  line
  line `(3) If a qualified person who has been served with a notice under sub-section (1) of section 13 or an`
  line `enlistment notice under section 14 leaves any employment in which he is engaged at the date of service of`
  line `such notice or is discharged therefrom otherwise than in accordance with the provisions of this Act, he or,`
  line `as the case may be, the person by whom he is discharged, shall be punished with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to five years and also with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (36082)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Persons required to register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36082&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every qualified person shall, if he is liable, at the`
  line `commencement of this Act, to be called up for national service, make an application, within ninety days`
  line `from such commencement, to be registered under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every qualified person who becomes liable after the commencement of this Act, to be called up`
  line `for national service, shall, within thirty days from the date on which he becomes so liable, make an`
  line `application to be registered under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (36083)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title Registration.
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36083&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by general order, direct qualified persons who`
  line `are required to be registered under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) to furnish at such place and time, in such manner and to such authority or person as may be`
  line `specified therein, such particulars about themselves as the order may require; and`
  line
  line `(b) to make at such place, in such manner and to such authority or person as may be specified in`
  line `the order, an application to be registered under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The order made under sub-section (1) may make different provisions in relation to different`
  line `classes of qualified persons subject to registration and may provide for exempting from any requirements`
  line `of the order of any class of qualified persons with respect to whom the Central Government is satisfied`
  line `that particulars sufficient for the purposes of this Act can be ascertained otherwise than by virtue of those`
  line requirements.
  line
  line `(3) If any qualified person fails to comply with any requirement of the order made under`
  line `sub-section (1), he shall be liable to be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three`
  line `years, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall ensure--`
  line
  line `(a) that upon an application duly made for registration under this Act, the name and address of`
  line `the applicant together with the particulars of the matters with respect to which information was given`
  line `by the applicant in pursuance of the order made under sub-section (1) are entered in a register kept for`
  line `the purposes of this Act, to be known as the "National Service Register"; and`
  line
  line `(b) that upon the applicant being registered, a certificate of registration is issued to the applicant`
  line `in the prescribed form.`
  line
  line `(5) The information contained in the National Service Register shall not be used for any purpose other`
  line `than the purposes of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall preclude the Central Government from disclosing, for`
  line `statistical purposes, any information contained in the National Service Register.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government may cause registration to be made of, and a certificate of registration to`
  line `be issued to, any qualified person of a class exempted from any of the requirements of sub-section (1) as`
  line `if that person had duly applied to be registered under this Act.`
  line
  line `(7) (a) If any qualified person subject to registration under this Act communicates to the Central`
  line `Government in the prescribed manner, that he has a preference for the Army, Air Force or Naval Service,`
  line `that fact shall be recorded in the National Service Register.`
  line
  line `(b) If a qualified person belonging to a class which is exempted from registration under this Act has a`
  line `preference for the Army, Air Force or Naval Service, he shall intimate such preference to the Central`
  line `Government in such manner as that Government may specify and, on receipt of such intimation, the`
  line `Central Government shall cause such preference to be recorded in the National Service Register.`
  line
  line `(8) (a) If any change occurs in the name or address of any qualified person while such person remains`
  line `registered under this Act, or if any such person acquires any additional academic or professional`
  line `qualification or distinction, he shall forthwith communicate the change of his name or address, or, as the`
  line `case may be, the acquisition by him of additional academic or professional qualification or distinction to`
  line `the Central Government in the prescribed manner and at the same time return to the Central Government,`
  line `for correction, any certificate of registration held by him and if he fails to communicate the change of his`
  line `name or address, or, as the case may be, the acquisition by him of the additional academic or professional`
  line `qualification or distinction, he shall be liable to be punished with fine which may extend to five hundred`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `(b) Upon the receipt of a communication of the change of name or address of any qualified person`
  line `registered under this Act or of acquisition by him of additional academic or professional qualification or`
  line `distinction, the Central Government shall cause the necessary corrections to be made in the entries in the`
  line `National Service Register and shall either cause the certificate to be corrected and returned to such person`
  line `or cause a fresh certificate to be issued to him.`
  line
  line `(9) The Central Government may, by rules made under this Act, provide for the issue, in specified`
  line `circumstances, of fresh certificates of registration in place of certificates which have been lost, destroyed`
  line `or defaced.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (36084)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Notice of likelihood of calling up for national service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36084&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may from`
  line `time to time cause to be served on any qualified person subject to registration under this Act, and, if he is`
  line `engaged in any employment, also on his employer, a written notice in the prescribed form stating that`
  line `such person is likely to be called upon, at any time within a period of twelve months next following, to`
  line `render national service.`
  line
  line `(2) Omission to serve any notice referred to in sub-section (1) on an employer or the service of such`
  line `notice on a person who is not, at the time of service of such notice, the employer of the qualified person`
  line `concerned, shall not invalidate the notice served under sub- section (1) on the qualified person and shall`
  line `not affect the liability of the qualified person to be called up for national service.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may cause to be served, on any qualified person served with a notice`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1), a written notice requiring that person to submit himself to an examination,`
  line `by such authority, at such place and at such time, as may be specified in the notice, of his physical and`
  line `mental fitness for being called up for national service.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may make regulations for the examination of the physical and mental`
  line `fitness of persons subject to registration under this Act and such regulations may, in particular, enable the`
  line `medical and other authority`
  line
  line `(a) in a case where he is unable to complete the examination on one occasion, to direct the person`
  line `examined to submit himself for a further examination on a specified time and place;`
  line
  line `(b) to direct the person examined to submit himself for examination by a specialist.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may by regulations determine the categories in which persons examined`
  line `under this section are to be placed with reference to their physical and mental condition.`
  line
  line `(6) If any qualified person fails to comply with the requirements of a notice served on him under`
  line `sub-section (3) or any regulations made or directions given under sub-section (4), he shall be liable to be`
  line `punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine which may extend`
  line `to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(7) The court by which a qualified person is convicted of an offence under this section may, without`
  line `prejudice to any penalty which may be imposed on him, order him to submit himself to an examination of`
  line `his physical and mental fitness, further examination or examination by a specialist, as the case may be, at`
  line `such place and at such time as may be fixed by the court and any such order may provide that such person`
  line `shall be detained in custody until that time and shall be taken by a police officer to that place and at that`
  line `time:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be detained in custody by virtue of any such order for more than`
  line `twenty-four hours.`
  line
  line `(8) A qualified person who, having been ordered by a court under sub-section (7) to submit himself to`
  line `an examination of his physical and mental fitness and to be detained in custody, is taken by a police`
  line `officer to the place and at the time at which he is to be examined, does not submit himself to an`
  line `examination of his physical and mental fitness in accordance with the order, he may be arrested by that or`
  line `any other police officer without a warrant.`
  line
  line `(9) A qualified person, who fails to submit himself to an examination of his physical and mental`
  line `fitness in accordance with an order made under sub-section (7), shall be liable to be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, and also with fine which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(10) A notice served on any qualified person under this section shall cease to have effect if, before`
  line `that date on which he is required to submit himself to an examination of his physical and mental fitness,`
  line `he ceases to be subject to registration under this Act.`
  line
  line `(11) The Central Government may pay to the medical or other authority, specialist, or any qualified`
  line `person undergoing examination of his physical and mental fitness under this section such travelling and`
  line `other allowances, including compensation for loss of remunerative time, in accordance with such scales`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (36085)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Enlistment for national service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36085&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such priorities as may be prescribed, the Central`
  line `Government may cause to be served on any qualified person for the time being liable under this Act to be`
  line `called up for national service, who has been found, after an examination of his physical and mental`
  line `condition, fit for such service, a written notice in the prescribed form (in this Act referred to as the`
  line `"enlistment notice") stating that he is called up for national service in such one of the Armed Forces of`
  line `the Union or in such other service as may be specified in the enlistment notice and requiring him to`
  line `present himself at such place and at such time and to such authority, as may be specified in the notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that an enlistment notice under this section shall not require the person upon whom it is`
  line `served to present himself on a day earlier than the fourteenth day after the date of service of the notice or`
  line `such earlier day as may be determined at his request.`
  line
  line `(2) An enlistment notice served on any qualified person shall cease to have effect if, before the day on`
  line `which he is thereby required to present himself, he ceases to be liable to be called up for national service`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may pay to persons required to present themselves in pursuance of an`
  line `enlistment notice served upon them travelling and other allowances in accordance with such scales as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) If on the day specified in the enlistment notice as the day on which the person to whom the notice`
  line `relates is required to present himself for national service--`
  line
  line `(a) a postponement certificate relating to him is in force, or`
  line
  line `(b) any appeal or application by him for postponement of national service is pending,`
  line `the enlistment notice served on him shall be of no effect.`
  line
  line `(5) The enlistment notice shall be served in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (36086)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Salary, wages, etc., and travelling allowances to be paid to persons enlisted for national service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36086&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every qualified person who is called up for national service under this Act, or who is`
  line `transferred from one form of national service to another, shall be paid such salary, wages, allowances,`
  line `pension, disability and death compensations and other benefits as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that such payments shall be on scales not less favourable than those admissible to persons of`
  line `like qualifications, experience and length of service in similar positions under the Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of the foregoing proviso, the length of standing of a qualified person`
  line `as an engineer or medical practitioner, as the case may be, shall be construed as the length of his service.`
  line
  line `(2) Any qualified person who is called up for national service or transferred from one form of`
  line `national service, or from one place of employment in the national service, to another, shall be paid`
  line `travelling allowance for journey to his place of employment under this Act at such rate as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) A qualified person who, on the date of the service of the enlistment notice on him, is engaged in`
  line `any employment, or a qualified person who is transferred from one form of national service, or from one`
  line `place of employment in the national service, to another, shall be paid, for the period of his transit from the`
  line `place of his former employment to the place of his employment under this Act, salary or wages (including`
  line `allowances) at the rate fixed by the Central Government under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) A qualified person who was in any employment on the date on which he was called up for`
  line `national service under this Act, shall, on his discharge from such service, be paid salary or wages`
  line `(including allowances) for the period of his transit from the place of his employment under this Act to the`
  line `place of his former employment at the rate fixed by the Central Government under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(5) A qualified person who is called up for national service under this Act shall, on the termination of`
  line `his national service, be paid travelling expenses at such rate as may be prescribed, for journey to the place`
  line `of his former employment, or, if he was unemployed when he was first called up for national service`
  line `under this Act, to the place of his residence.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (36087)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title Training.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36087&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `During his term of national service a qualified person may be required to undergo`
  line `training for such period as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (36088)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title Discharge.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36088&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every qualified person enlisted under this Act shall be entitled to receive his`
  line `discharge from national service on the expiration of the period for which he was enlisted and such person`
  line `may, prior to the expiration of that period, be discharged from national service by such authority and`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A person receiving discharge under this section shall be given a certificate in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed certifying that he has been discharged from national service.`
  line
  line `(3) A person who has received discharge under this section shall not be required to render national`
  line `service after such discharge:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person who has received discharge under this section before he has completed four`
  line `years of national service, shall, unless he has ceased to be liable to be called up for national service under`
  line `this Act, be liable to be called up for national service under this Act for such term as will, together with`
  line `the period of national service rendered by him, be equivalent to four years.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (36089)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `National Service (Hardship) Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36089&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall constitute a`
  line `National Service (Hardship) Committee consisting of a Chairman and two other members appointed by it.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman of the National Service (Hardship) Committee shall be a person who is, or has`
  line `been, or is qualified to be, a Judge of a High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) The members of the National Service (Hardship) Committee shall hold office for a period of three`
  line `years but shall be eligible for reappointment.`
  line
  line `(4) The proceedings of the National Service (Hardship) Committee shall not be invalid by reason of`
  line `any defect in the constitution of, or any vacancy in, such Committee.`
  line
  line `(5) Any vacancy in the National Service (Hardship) Committee shall be filled by the Central`
  line `Government in such manner as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government may constitute Regional National Service (Hardship) Committees for`
  line `such regions as it may think fit and on such constitution such Regional National Service (Hardship)`
  line `Committees shall have all the powers, functions and privileges of the National Service (Hardship)`
  line `Committee and shall be subject to the same provisions as are applicable to that Committee.`
  line
  line `(7) The National Service (Hardship) Committee shall have power to regulate its own procedure with`
  line `regard to any investigation under this Act and shall have for the purposes of such investigation the powers`
  line `of a civil court while trying a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the`
  line `following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents producible as evidence;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on oath;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(e) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (36090)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Application for postponement on grounds of hardship.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36090&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any qualified person who is for`
  line `the time being liable to be called up for national service under this Act and who has been served with a`
  line `notice referred to in sub-section (1) of section 13, or any employer of such qualified person, may apply, in`
  line `the prescribed manner to the Central Government for a certificate of postponement of liability to be called`
  line `up for national service on the ground that exceptional hardship would ensue if such qualified person were`
  line `called up for national service, and may, on that ground apply, in the prescribed manner, for the renewal of`
  line `the postponement certificate granted to him.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an application for a postponement certificate or for the renewal thereof is made, the Central`
  line `Government shall refer the application for decision to the National Service (Hardship) Committee.`
  line
  line `(3) No application for the grant of a postponement certificate shall be referred by the Central`
  line `Government to the National Service (Hardship) Committee unless such application is made within sixty`
  line `days from the date of service of the notice referred to in sub-section (1) of section 13:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may refer an application for the grant of a postponement`
  line `certificate to the National Service (Hardship) Committee made after the expiry of the said period if it is`
  line `satisfied, having regard to the grounds on which the application is made, that the making thereof has not`
  line `been unreasonably delayed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may by regulations specify the principles to be applied and the`
  line `circumstances to which regard is to be or not to be had for the hearing of an application for the grant or`
  line `renewal of a postponement certificate and as to the period for which the postponement certificate may be`
  line `granted or renewed.`
  line
  line `(5) The National Service (Hardship) Committee may, after consideration of the application for a`
  line `postponement certificate or renewal thereof, grant or reject the same.`
  line
  line `(6) The period within which the postponement certificate is in force shall be added to the period`
  line `during which the person to whom the certificate was granted is liable under this Act to be called up for`
  line `national service and accordingly this Act shall in relation to that person have effect as if for reference`
  line `therein to the age of thirty years, there were substituted, an age being the sum of thirty years and the`
  line `period during which--`
  line
  line `(i) the postponement certificate is in force, and`
  line
  line `(ii) the enlistment notice was of no effect by reason of the provisions of clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 14.`
  line
  line `(7) If any qualified person or an employer makes an application for a postponement certificate on a`
  line `ground which he knows to be false or does not believe to be true or on a ground which, in the opinion of`
  line `the National Service (Hardship) Committee, is frivolous, he shall be liable to be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend to one thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (36091)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Appeal from decision of the National Service (Hardship) Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36091&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2), an appeal shall lie against the decision of the National Service (Hardship)`
  line `Committee to the High Court exercising jurisdiction in relation to the territory in which the applicant for`
  line `the postponement certificate voluntarily resides, carries on business or personally works for gain.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal referred to in sub-section (1) shall lie unless--`
  line
  line `(i) it is preferred within thirty days from the date of the decision of the National Service`
  line `(Hardship) Committee, and`
  line
  line `(ii) the National Service (Hardship) Committee certifies that the case involves a substantial`
  line `question of law.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the National Service (Hardship) Committee has refused to give a certificate referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2), the High Court may, if it is satisfied that the case involves a substantial question of law,`
  line `grant special leave to appeal against the decision of the National Service (Hardship) Committee.`
  line
  line `(4) The High Court may, after hearing the appeal, confirm, modify or reverse the decision of the`
  line `National Service (Hardship) Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (36092)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Revocation of postponement certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36092&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, at any time, while a postponement certificate is`
  line `in force, it appears to the Central Government that, by reason of any change in the circumstances of the`
  line `qualified person to whom the certificate was granted or of his employer, where such certificate was`
  line `granted on the application of such employer, the certificate ought to be revoked or the period for which it`
  line `was granted or last renewed ought to be shortened, the Central Government may apply to the National`
  line `Service (Hardship) Committee, and that Committee may either reject the application or cancel the`
  line `certificate or vary it by shortening the period.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an application is made under sub-section (1), the person to whom the postponement`
  line `certificate in question was granted, and where such certificate was granted on the application of an`
  line `employer, such employer, shall be entitled to be heard on the application and the provisions as to appeals`
  line `contained in section 20 shall apply in relation to the application as if it were an application for the grant of`
  line `a postponement certificate.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (36093)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Suspension of right to postponement of liability to be called up for national service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36093&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Government may, if it is satisfied at any time that by reason of the gravity of the situation it is`
  line `necessary so to do, by order--`
  line
  line `(a) cancel, either generally or in relation to a specified class of qualified persons, all`
  line `postponement certificates in force at the date of the order, and`
  line
  line `(b) abrogate, either generally or in relation to a specified class of qualified persons, any right to`
  line `apply for the grant of a postponement certificate and any right to appeal from the refusal to grant such`
  line `a certificate, and may, by order, vary or revoke any order in force under this section, without`
  line `prejudice however to the previous effect of that order.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, on the day on which an order comes into force under this section abrogating any right to`
  line `appeal from the refusal to grant a postponement certificate, an appeal preferred by a person to whom the`
  line `order applies or the time for preferring such appeal by such person has not expired, the appeal shall be`
  line `deemed to be dismissed or the time shall be deemed to expire on the expiry of that day.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (36094)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title Reinstatement.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36094&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "former employee" means a qualified person who was released by an employer for`
  line `employment in national service;`
  line
  line `(b) "former employer" means the employer by whom a former employee was employed in an`
  line `establishment immediately before the enlistment of such employee for national service;`
  line
  line `(c) "former employment" means the employment in which the former employee was employed`
  line `immediately before his enlistment for national service.`
  line
  line `(2) (a) A former employee may, on the termination of his national service, make an application in`
  line `such manner and within such period as may be prescribed to his former employer for reinstatement in his`
  line `former employment.`
  line
  line `(b) On receipt of an application referred to in clause (a), the former employer shall be under an`
  line `obligation (unless the employment of the former employee in the national service was terminated by`
  line `dismissal for misconduct) to reinstate such employee before the expiry of a period of fifteen days from`
  line `the date of receipt of such application.`
  line
  line `(3) (a) If, on receipt of an application referred to in sub-section (2), the former employer refuses to`
  line `reinstate the applicant on the ground that his circumstances have so changed as to make it impossible or`
  line `unreasonable for him to do so, or denies his liability to reinstate such former employee, or represents that`
  line `the reinstatement by him of the former employee is impracticable, he shall, before the expiry of a period`
  line `of fifteen days from the date of receipt of such application, make an application to the National Service`
  line `(Hardship) Committee for relieving him from the obligation referred to in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(b) A former employee, who is not reinstated in his former employment within fifteen days from the`
  line `date of delivery of the application made under sub-section (2), may, within a further period of fifteen days`
  line `(computed from the date on which the first-mentioned period of fifteen days expires), represent to the`
  line `National Service (Hardship) Committee that his former employer has not discharged the obligation`
  line `imposed on him by sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(c) On receipt of the application referred to in clause (a) or the representation referred to in clause (b),`
  line `the National Service (Hardship) Committee shall, after considering all matters placed before it and after`
  line `making such inquiry in the matter as it may think fit, make an order--`
  line
  line `(i) relieving the former employer from the obligation referred to in sub-section (2), or`
  line
  line `(ii) requiring the former employer to reinstate the former employee in his former employment, or`
  line
  line `(iii) requiring the former employer to pay to the former employee by way of compensation, for`
  line `failure or inability to reinstate him, a sum not exceeding an amount equal to six months remuneration`
  line `at the rate at which remuneration was last payable by the former employer to the former employee.`
  line
  line `(d) Where the National Service (Hardship) Committee has directed the reinstatement of any person in`
  line `his former employment, the former employer shall be under an obligation to pay to such person salary`
  line `and allowances at the rates specified by the National Service (Hardship) Committee from the date of`
  line `receipt of the application referred to in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) (a) A former employer, who has refused to reinstate his former employee on any of the grounds`
  line `specified in sub-section (3) and who has omitted or failed, without any reasonable excuse, to make an`
  line `application to the National Service (Hardship) Committee within the time specified in sub-section (3),`
  line
  line `shall be punished, without any prejudice to the provisions of clause (b) of this sub-section, with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month, or with fine which may extend to five thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(b) If any former employer fails to obey any order made by the National Service (Hardship)`
  line `Committee under sub-section (3), he shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `one month, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both, and the court by which`
  line `such former employer is convicted under this sub-section shall order him to pay to the person whom he`
  line `has failed to re-employ, a sum not exceeding an amount equal to six months' remuneration at the rate at`
  line `which his last remuneration was payable to him by the former employer and any amount so required to be`
  line `paid shall be recoverable as if it were a fine imposed by such court.`
  line
  line `(5) Where in pursuance of the provisions of sub-section (2) a former employer reinstates his former`
  line `employee and thereafter terminates the employment of such former employee at any time within a period`
  line `of six months from the date of such reinstatement, the former employer shall, notwithstanding anything to`
  line `the contrary contained in the conditions of employment of the former employee, be liable to pay to the`
  line `former employee, at the time of terminating his employment as aforesaid, a sum equal to the`
  line `remuneration which the former employee would have earned under the terms and conditions of his`
  line `re-employment for the unexpired portion of the said period of six months:`
  line
  line `Provided that a former employer shall not be liable to make such payment as aforesaid where the`
  line `employment of the former employee is terminated for the reason that the former employee has been guilty`
  line `of gross insubordination, habitual absence from work or any serious misconduct or has been convicted of`
  line `any offence:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a former employee whose employment is terminated within the said period for`
  line `any such reason as aforesaid may refer the matter to the National Service (Hardship) Committee and that`
  line `Committee shall, after due consideration, decide whether or not the employer is liable as aforesaid under`
  line `this sub-section; and any such decision shall be final and binding on the parties.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Any sum required to be paid under this sub-section shall be in addition to the amount,`
  line `if any, which the employer may, under the conditions of employment be liable to pay in respect of the`
  line `termination of the employment of the former employee without notice.`
  line
  line `(6) No change in the name, constitution or character of the former employer shall affect the right of`
  line `reinstatement of a former employee who has been released from employment in national service.`
  line
  line `(7) (a) The occupation in which and the terms and conditions under which a qualified person may be`
  line `reinstated after completion of national service shall not be less favourable to him than those which would`
  line `have been applicable to him had his employment not been interrupted by reason of his being called up for`
  line `national service.`
  line
  line `(b) In determining the terms and conditions of reinstatement of the former employee, regard shall be`
  line `had to the additional skill and experience acquired by such employee in the course of his employment in`
  line `the national service.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (36095)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Preservation of certain rights of qualified persons required to render national service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36095&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `While any qualified person, required to render national service under this Act, has any rights under any`
  line `provident fund or other scheme for the benefit of employees maintained in connection with the`
  line `employment he relinquishes, he shall continue, so long as he is engaged in national service and if he is`
  line `reinstated, until such reinstatement under the provisions of this Act, to have in respect of such fund or`
  line `scheme such rights as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (36096)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `False statement and forgery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36096&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any qualified person`
  line
  line `(a) on whom an enlistment notice has been served under this Act in respect of whom no`
  line `postponement certificate is in force or no application or appeal for postponement of national service`
  line `is pending, fails or omits to render the service which he is required by such notice to render, or`
  line
  line `(b) having commenced to render national service, leaves that service without obtaining a`
  line `discharge under section 17,`
  line
  line `he shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years and also with fine`
  line `which may extend to two thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who`
  line
  line `(a) in giving any information for the purposes of this Act, knowingly or recklessly makes a`
  line `statement which is false in material particulars or which he does not believe to be true, or`
  line
  line `(b) (i) with the intention of deceiving, forges or uses or lends or allows to be used for any person`
  line `any certificate issued under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(ii) makes, or has in his possession, any document so closely resembling any certificate so issued`
  line `as to be calculated to deceive,`
  line
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment for a term not exceeding three years, or with fine not exceeding one`
  line `thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (36097)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `General provision as to offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36097&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Any qualified person who contravenes any provision of this`
  line `Act for the contravention of which no penalty is separately specified in this Act, shall be punished with`
  line `fine which may extend to five hundred rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any proceedings for an offence punishable under this section, it shall be a defence for`
  line `the accused to prove that he was prevented from complying with the provisions of this Act by`
  line `circumstances beyond his control.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (36098)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36098&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any provision of this Act or of any order made thereunder is`
  line `contravened by a company, every person who at the time the contravention was made was in charge of,`
  line `and was responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the`
  line `company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the contravention and shall be liable to be proceeded against`
  line `and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any such offence has been`
  line `committed and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or connivance, or is`
  line `attributable to, any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the`
  line `company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of that offence`
  line `and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (36099)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Information to be furnished by Universities, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36099&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every University or`
  line `other persons having the management of any University, school or other educational institution, to give to`
  line `the Central Government, at its request, such information in their possession, or reasonably available to`
  line `them, about persons receiving, or who have received education in engineering, technology, medical`
  line `sciences or surgery as the Central Government may, by notification, specify in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (36100)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Information to be furnished by District Magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36100&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every District`
  line `Magistrate to give to the State Government such information in his possession about qualified persons`
  line `within the local limits of his jurisdiction as may be prescribed, and it shall be the duty of every State`
  line `Government to give to the Central Government all information in its possession about qualified persons in`
  line `the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (36101)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Priority of debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36101&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Presidency Towns`
  line `Insolvency Act, 1909 (3 of 1909), the Provincial Insolvency Act, 1920 (5 of 1920), the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956), or the Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932), any compensation payable under this Act shall`
  line `have priority over all other unsecured debts.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (36102)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Summary trial of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36102&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), every offence punishable under this Act shall be tried summarily.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (36103)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Jurisdiction to try offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36103&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `No court inferior to that of a Presidency Magistrate or a`
  line `Magistrate of the first class shall try any offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (36104)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36104&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance`
  line `of this Act or any rules, regulations or orders made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government for any damage caused`
  line `or likely to be caused for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this`
  line `Act or any rules, regulations or orders made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (36105)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Removal of difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36105&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `the Central Government may make such order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may`
  line `appear to it to be necessary for the purpose or removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this sub-section after the expiry of a period of two years`
  line `from the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) shall be laid before both Houses of Parliament as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made and the provisions of section 38 shall apply to such order as if it were a rule made`
  line `under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (36106)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Powers to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36106&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, direct that all or any of the`
  line `powers which may be exercised by it under this Act shall, in such circumstances and under such`
  line `conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification, be exercised also by any State Government or`
  line `any other authority owned or controlled by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (36107)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36107&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for`
  line `carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the principles governing the calling up of persons for national service;`
  line
  line `(b) the form and contents of the National Service Register;`
  line
  line `(c) the form in which the certificate of registration is to be issued;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of notification of preference for any branch of the Armed Forces of the Union;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of notification of change of name or address of, or acquisition of academic or`
  line `professional qualification or distinctions by, a qualified person registered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) the circumstances under which fresh certificates of registration in place of certificates which`
  line `have been lost, destroyed or defaced may be issued;`
  line
  line `(g) the form and contents of the notice for examination of physical and mental fitness;`
  line
  line `(h) the scale in accordance with which travelling and other allowances may be paid to medical or`
  line `other authority or specialist or to any qualified person undergoing any examination of physical and`
  line `mental fitness and the scale according to which compensation may be paid for loss of remunerative`
  line time;
  line
  line `(i) the priorities in accordance with which qualified persons may be enlisted for national service;`
  line
  line `(j) the form and contents of the enlistment notice and the manner of service thereof;`
  line
  line `(k) the scales of salary, wages, allowances, pensions, disability and death compensations and`
  line `other financial benefits admissible to those performing national service;`
  line
  line `(l) the scales of travelling allowances required to be paid under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) the authority by which and conditions subject to which prior discharge from national service`
  line `may be made;`
  line
  line `(n) the form of discharge certificate;`
  line
  line `(o) the manner of application for a certificate of postponement of liability to be called up for`
  line `national service or for renewal thereof and the time within which such application for renewal should`
  line `be made;`
  line
  line `(p) the conditions of reinstatement of persons released from employment in the national service`
  line `and matters connected therewith;`
  line
  line `(q) further inquiry which may be made by the National Service (Hardship) Committee where`
  line `reinstatement of qualified persons released from employment in the national service is refused or`
  line `denied or where such reinstatement is represented to be impracticable;`
  line
  line `(r) the preservation of rights of provident fund, etc., of qualified persons rendering national`
  line service;
  line
  line `(s) the information relating to qualified persons which every District Magistrate shall furnish to`
  line `the State Government;`
  line
  line `(t) any other matter which is required to be, or may be prescribed under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Any rule made under this Act may provide that a contravention of the rule shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term not exceeding six months, or with fine not exceeding one thousand rupees, or`
  line `with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (36108)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36108&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may make regulations not inconsistent`
  line `with this Act, to provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) enabling or requiring a qualified person to be transferred to any branch of the Armed Forces`
  line `of the Union or to any other branch of national service;`
  line
  line `(b) examination of physical and mental fitness of qualified persons subject to registration under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) determination of the categories in which qualified persons whose physical and mental fitness`
  line `has been examined shall be placed by reference to their physical or mental conditions or both;`
  line
  line `(d) specification of the principles to be applied and the circumstances to be considered while`
  line `hearing an application for the grant or renewal of a postponement certificate;`
  line
  line `(e) specification of the period for which a postponement certificate may be granted or renewed;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter for which regulations are required to be, or may be, made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (36109)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827&sectionId=36109&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_53_00001_197228_1517807320827
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made by`
  line `the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `to the rule or regulation or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or`
  line `regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be;`
  line `so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
